  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="thebulletwasagirl"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="narrative"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="death"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
               <l>the bullet is his whole life.</l>
               <l>his mother named him &amp; the bullet</l>
               
               <l>was on its way. in another life</l>
               <l>the bullet was a girl &amp; his skin</l>
               
               <l>was a boy with a sad laugh.</l>
               <l>they say he asked for it—</l>
               
               <l>must I define they? they are not</l>
               <l>monsters, or hooded or hands black</l>
               
               <l>with cross smoke.</l>
               <l>they teachers, they pay tithes</l>
               
               <l>they like rap, they police—good folks</l>
               <l>gather around a boy’s body</l>
               
               <l>to take a picture, share a prayer.</l>
               <l>oh da horror, oh what a shame</l>
               
               <l>why’d he do that to himself?</l>
               <l>they really should stop</l>
               <l>getting themselves killed</l>
                 
                 
